Sheâ€™s a Park Explorer at Pumpkin Hill Creek Preserve State Park - CSA
Grades: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12

Many different plants and animals live together in healthy ecosystems. At Pumpkin Hill Creek Preserve State Park, rangers are working to restore the health of longleaf pine forest ecosystems within the preserve. Learn techniques to transform a planted pine plantation back into a native sandhill or pine flatwood community including vegetation surveys, tree thinning, prescribed fire and seedling planting. Hands-on activities will include plant identification along a guided nature hike, wetland faunal sampling, and a fire engine demonstration. Fun patch provided. Park entrance fee included.

*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts, and registered & approved adult volunteers.
* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings. 
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event. 
*Event registration closes Feb. 1

$8/girl, $8/adult
Contact: Brittany McCallister 904.389.3071
